## Cross-cutting facts & pitfalls (matters from day one)

- **Generator ≠ judge / reviewer = input, not authority.** The deterministic gate (tests / judge / cross-model review) is the source of honesty, not any single model — so a model can be weak or hallucinating but cannot fake a verdict.
- **Trust code + graph over docs** — stale README / PROJECT_MAP / frozen memory layers describe a past epoch.
- **The target is READ-ONLY**; `src/` changes need approve + reviewer + the test gate GREEN; `{{PR_TARGET}}` is protected.
- **GRACE governance is on** (`grace/` + the pilot branch `{{GRACE_PILOT}}`). The AI-assistant discipline is in `grace/AI-BRIEF.md`.
